programme.title: Two Chances at an Indiana Bruiser, November has Arrived

programme.title: Kansas Youth Opener, The Next Generation

programme.title: TINY HOMES

programme.title: MOUNTAIN FITNESS

programme.title: MOUNTAIN SURVIVAL

programme.title: TROUBLESHOOTING BACKCOUNTRY OBSTACLES
programme.desc: Traversing the rugged mountains has its challenges and it's beneficial to be prepared. Join Laura on the backend of this 2 part series as she focuses on conquering backcountry obstacles.

programme.title: MAKING PEMMICAN
programme.desc: In an effort to find an alternative to an all butter backcountry diet, Laura leans towards Pemmican, an original survival food made by many Native American tribes.

programme.title: TROPICAL SURVIVAL

programme.title: AVALANCHE

programme.title: CAR ACCIDENTS

programme.title: TORNADO

programme.title: EXTREME HEAT

programme.title: Hunting with a Lost Lemming: Okayest Hunter's 2022 deer hunting season kickoff!
programme.desc:
The crew from the Okayest Hunter podcast thought it'd be a good idea to start a hunting show, but they wanted to do something different, and it needed to align with the brand, mission, and ethos of the Okayest Hunter. Basically, it can't be too serious. So we thought, hey, let's make the "Office" show, but for hunting.
Our hunting season is chock full of humility as we miss place things, take too long to pick out our tree, injure ourselves, miss deer, lose arrows, and more. However, we had one of our best and most fun seasons yet! Follow along as we release new episodes as our 2022 deer hunting season unfolds. We assure you it'll be worth getting all the way to the end!
Cheers to chasing shooter bucks in the deer woods and never passing on what makes you happy! We hope you can relate as we share our shenanigans with everyone!
Okayest Hunter Show, season one: We'll See How it Goes, Episode one: Hunting with a lost lemming.

programme.title: Spring Turkey Extravaganza [Part II]
programme.desc: After Eric shot his first bird in part I of the Okayest Hunter's first turkey hunt, he get's to do all the other firsts with his gobbler. Eric learns what a limb hanger is, or in this case isn't. He also learns how to field dress his first turkey.

programme.title: Early season Fox Trapping
programme.desc: Bryan hangs out with fellow trappers in Pennsylvania to trap opening week of the season.

programme.title: Land Trapping 101
programme.desc: The Fur life teaches you all about Land Trapping. From Bobcat to Fox and everything in between.

programme.title: Trapping Life
programme.desc: Corey talks about his love of trapping. His son Brody is also on the line having fun catching critters, such as badgers, bobcat, coyote, raccoons and more

programme.title: Pope and Young
programme.desc: Corey talks about his first Pope and young experience. A tale about the heart pounding moment we all dream of feeling as a huge buck heads your way. This Wisconsin Giant makes the mistake of walking into close range.

programme.title: Missouri Monarch
programme.desc: A long lost story about the One Giant buck that gave Corey Brossman the Buck Fever. While Freelancing for Matt Morrett in Missouri a Giant buck steps into the field. After a few deep breaths, Corey gets his composer together and lays down some amazing footage.

programme.title: Hunting with a Country Legend
programme.desc: Corey talks about his hunt with country music legend Tracy Lawrence. They're chasing BIG buck at the famous Tecomate Ranch in Texas

programme.title: Pop Pop's Hog Hunting
programme.desc: Corey talks about his hunt with his Pop Pop. Hog hunting in North Carolina for wild hog. Pop Pop and Corey Double up on big pigs with the 7mm

programme.title: Bowfishing Flying Fish
programme.desc: Corey tells an old tale about Flying fish and shooting them with bowfishing gear. These Asian Carp fly into the air making them great targets on the Illinois River. The arrows are flying and the guys are having fun.

programme.title: Shed Wars
programme.desc: Corey meets up with Rick Cruter from Beyond to hunt TV. They're bowhunting in Ohio for Giant Whitetails. The location in which they're hunting isn't normal. In fact, its almost Like Shed Hunting!!

programme.title: The OMG Buck
programme.desc: Corey's wife drops the hammer on a massive 170 inch 10 point in the land of OZ. This is a story on how the OMG buck ended up open the Brossman's wall back in Pennsylvania.

programme.title: BOWFISHING BONANZA PART II
programme.desc: Jana is back in Texas with AMS Bowfishing's Matt Schillinger. It's an action packed couple of days hunting hogs, turkey, and a giant alligator gar!

programme.title: Bowfishing Zimbabwe Crocodile
programme.desc: One of the coolest shots ever filmed with a bow and arrow. You don't want to miss this exciting Crocodile hunt from Zimbabwe. Follow along as VP of AMS Bowfishing Jeff Braun tucks away in a ground blind and waits patiently for a shot of a lifetime at an African Crocodile. The AMS gear does exactly what its meant to do.

programme.title: Giants in Green Bay
programme.desc: Mathew is joined by Cindy Braun the CEO of AMS Bowfishing as they travel to Green Bay Wisconsin in pursuit of giant common carp. Also known as Title Town USA home of the Green Bay Packers but also giant Carp. Also known for its world class Walleye fishing, these invasive carp must be kept in check as they destroy spawning habitat for the native fish. Non-stop bowfishing action as the Giants of Green Bay move into the shallows and make for some great night time bowfishing.

programme.title: Where The Buffalo Roam Part 1
programme.desc: In this episode Mathew heads down to Kentucky to meet up with Dennis Redden in pursuit of big buffalo. As the suns rays warm up the water temperatures the action picks up and they connect on a giant 74 pounder.

programme.title: Lake Poygan Walleyes
programme.desc: This week on Larry Smith Outdoors we hit Lake Poygan for a two day Walleye bite. We brought Terry from BiteMeBox and I even had two of my kids (Isaac, Sawyer, and his Girlfriend Jen) out on the lake. Unbelievable Walleye bite for beginnings of new ICE! Check out the motherload of fish we caught!

programme.title: How to catch Crappies on Basin lakes Ice fishing
programme.desc: LEARN how to catch more basin crappies ice fishing! On this week's episode we head over to Chippewa county to hook up with Andrew from Backroads Guide Service! Andrew has been a long time friend of the show and an awesome fishing guide! He puts us on a great basin crappie bites and shows us some great tips on how you can catch more!

programme.title: Jeff Guilloz
programme.desc: Aloha! This is our debut show here on Carbon TV! In this Episode, meet Jeff Guilloz as he Hunts on a nearby farm here on the island of Hawaii and confronts a family of wild pigs. Join Jeff and he shows you His Hawaii and all of the beauty that surrounds him.

programme.title: Fishing and Crabbing Hawaiian style
programme.desc: Jeff, Barry and friends head down south for some fishing and crabbing, Hawaiian Style. Check um out!

programme.title: Bulls, Bucks, & Beards!
programme.desc: Crafting the ultimate outdoor experience is Rick Taylor's cup of tea. Rick is a lifetime outdoorsman and currently works for BPI Outdoors as their Social Media Strategist. In this episode, he shares his passion for hunting, guiding and just being outdoors. He has had the opportunity to guide elk hunts in Tennessee, pass his love of hunting to his kids, and help his dad harvest his first buck later in life. This is a must-watch if you love hunting. Don't miss it!

programme.title: A Turkey Hunt Goes South in the Florida Swamp
programme.desc:
Welcome to Season 1, Episode 3 of Seek and Find TV! This episode is all about chasing a turkey through a Florida swamp! Reese and Amber decided to let Scott, guide them through their home turf (aka the swamp) since he's the expert turkey caller, and what happened was a disaster! He found the turkey.... but he also found out how quick things can go south in the swamp! This turkey hunting episode will for sure have you laughing and keep you excited the whole time!
Seek and Find TV was founded by Scott Hinnant of Conviction Outdoors and Reese Richards of Bearded Outdoors. The two friends came together and decided to create an outdoor show with a twist of Jesus. They equally share a love and passion for all things hunting, fishing, and anything in the outdoors, but what really brought these two together is their love for Jesus and passion to spread His name. Scott resides in Mississippi and Reese in Florida, so the episodes for Seek and Find TV will have a good variety of scenery and things to do in the outdoors.

Not Another Black Movie stars Damon Williams (Bad Boys of Comedy, Comic View, BET LIVE, The Tom Joyner Morning Show), Janet Hubert (The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air), Rodney Perry (The Monique Show, Who's Got Jokes) Jay Davis (Not Another Zombie Movie, Shots Fired), and Leon Rogers (WGCI, Comic View, Bad Boys of Comedy).
Not Another Black Movie is not only a spoof of a genre often associated with Tyler Perry films, but a satirical look at family dysfunction as well. Written by Jay Davis and Directed by Donte "Diesel" Williams, Not Another Black Movie addresses issues that effect many families whether they be rich or poor, black or white. Although we poke fun at some of the stereotypical roles portrayed in this genre, we hope to shed some light on problems that plague many families while giving you a good laugh.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E05 - Juno, Cassini and Beyond
programme.desc: The Cassini space craft has completed its mission over Saturn, Juno has reached its target and has commenced its scientific observations of the giant planet Jupiter. and The New Horizons speeds on it its next encounter at the edge of the solar system.

programme.title: The New Frontier - S03:E06 - Sling Shot
programme.desc: Sending probes throughout the solar system is a mathematicians dream and an engineers nightmare, sling shotting probes around other planets to arrive at their destination, we checkout the latest probes about to slingshot about the solar system.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E10 - Close Protection
programme.desc: From the elite ex-special forces personnel in charge of guarding heads of state in conflict zones to the two-person teams that protect CEOs in dangerous regions, modern day bodyguards must be well versed in close quarter battle techniques. An immense amount of planning and preparation is involved in each operation. From air travel, car convoys and helicopter shuttles to basic foot traffic, a close protection squad must be completely tuned to the Who, What, Where and When of any given situation. This episode of CQB focuses on the complex day-to-day and minute-to-minute operations of these elite teams and the highly developed techniques they employ.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E13 - William And Kate One Year On
programme.desc: William and Catherine got married in a fairytale ceremony on April 29, 2011, with more than two billion people tuning in and celebrations happening all around the world.

programme.desc: Meghan Markle and Prince Harry share similar interests and seem like a perfect match. Both have faced tough times growing up but have come out on top. Now they're winning together. This hour-long special, featuring a chat with author Andrew Morton, explores the social backdrop that makes their bold marriage fit right in with today's British Royal Family.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E11 - Counter Terrorism
programme.desc: Following the September 11 attacks, military presence became commonplace in New York and other American cities, and the counter terrorism forces were effectively given a “blank cheque” when it came to ensuring that another terrorist incident would never take place on American soil. This episode of CQB takes an in–depth look at who was selected to occupy elite anti-terrorist positions, what they were trained for, and how they were equipped: when opposing forces are using commercial airliners and chemical weapons, countermeasures are by necessity complicated and varied. CQB takes an intimate look at what it was like to be an officer on alert for chemical attacks in Washington DC, or an army reservist monitoring suspicious activities on the streets of NYC.

programme.title: Close Quarter Battle - S01:E12 - French Foreign Legion
programme.desc: No country other than France operates an elite military force that invites foreign nationals to serve in its ranks. With a reputation for being a safe haven for individuals with questionable pasts, the French Foreign Legion is a true mercenary army that has garnered significant respect within the global special operations community. This episode of CQB examines a raid by the Foreign Legion on a small airport in Iraq during the 1990 Gulf War, exploring the nature of the Legion, how it differs from other special forces, and how it prepares for a wide variety of close quarter battle scenarios in conflict situations around the world.

programme.desc: Ivan joins the foremost anti-poaching team in Mozambique to bring down one particular group of poachers who have been killing local elephants for their ivory.

programme.title: Wild Ones - S01:E05 - Strongest
programme.desc: How do you decide which is the strongest animal on the Planet? Wild Ones looks at the comparative strength of the tiniest of ants to that of a might grizzly bear, or a deadly crocodile to the indestructible rhinoceros.

programme.title: Wild Ones - S01:E06 - Cutest
programme.desc: The charming kangaroo. The cuddly koala. The beautiful butterfly. The cheerful clownfish. Or the adorable budgie - which one is the cutest of them all?

programme.title: Wild Ones - S01:E07 - Wild Australia
programme.desc: More than 80 percent of Australia’s plants, mammals, reptiles and frogs are unique to Australia and are found nowhere else in the world. Wild dingos, frisky kangaroos, deceptively cuddly looking koalas and playful platypuses are some of the most iconic of Australia’s wild animals.

programme.title: Wild Ones - S01:E08 - Masters of the Sky
programme.desc: So many words describe the many ways that birds fly – pelicans and kestrels soar but owls fly silently. Parrots flock, vultures swarm and eagles swoop. Radar-accurate eyes scan the ground and slotted feathers adjust flight paths as hawks attack. But, which is the true master of the sky?

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S02:E02- Naturally Noble
programme.desc: Zimbabwe was initially Southern Rhodesia and lies to the south of the Victoria Falls along the river Zambezi. Zambia was initially Northern Rhodesia and lies on the other bank of the river. Zimbabwe is a landlocked country in the south-east of Africa. It borders with South Africa to the south. According to archaeologists, the earliest records indicate that first human settlements in this area reach back to the 3rd century.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S02:E03 - Naturally Sustaining
programme.desc: We journey in search of incredible miracles of nature begins on the Canary Islands. Lanzarote is of a volcanic origin. Volcanic activity created a fantastical landscape, similar to that on Mars. On Gran Canarias we will witness a traditional harvest of a crop that has been brought to the rest of the world from here - sugarcane. We will wrap up this episode in the Moroccan province of Gulemin, a home to a nomadic tribe whose inseparable companions are camels.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S02:E04 - Naturally Colourful
programme.desc: Venture into the Mexican seaside state of Veracruz in the south-west of the country and admire the unbelievable colours of locally grown orchids. Find out how vanilla is grown and discover how brown sugar is made. To top things off, witness an extraordinary ritual. Later, we will visit the Cayman Islands in the Caribbean. The three islands are relatively small but are inhabited by some remarkable animals including sea turtles, friendly rays and other types of fish as well as fascinating blue iguanas.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S02:E05 - Naturally Enigmatic
programme.desc: Today we will visit three remarkable nooks of Europe in search of miracles of nature. To begin with, we will venture into Austria's Salzburg region. An area that is famous for its Alps and Tauern mountains but also because it is the birth place of Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart. After that, we will move over to the south western outpost of the old continent, to Portugal's Algarve region. To conclude, we will admire Corsica, the French island of beauty.

programme.desc: Laramy embraces the challeges presented when hunting Whitetail deer in Montana.

programme.title: Sasquatch Mountain Man - S04:E11 - Moose
programme.desc: Laramy has spotted some huge moose, now he just needs to hope his Hawken shoots straight and true!

programme.title: Sasquatch Mountain Man - S04:E12 - Bear Part 2
programme.desc: The bigger the challenge, the bigger the reward as Laramy continues his hunt for bear in the Rockies.

programme.title: Sasquatch Mountain Man - S04:E13 - Hunt of a Mountain Man
programme.desc: Laramy shows us how hunting was done in the mid 1800s by the Mountain Men, where unusual skills and stalking techniques were needed to survive throughout the winter. Harsh Winters were known as White Death to the Mountain Men.

programme.desc: More than 80 percent of Australia’s plants, mammals, reptiles and frogs are unique to Australia and are found nowhere else in the world. Wild dingos, frisky kangaroos, deceptively cuddly looking koalas and playful platypuses are some of the most iconic of Australia’s wild animals.

programme.title: Wild Ones - S01:E08 - Masters of the Sky
programme.desc: So many words describe the many ways that birds fly – pelicans and kestrels soar but owls fly silently. Parrots flock, vultures swarm and eagles swoop. programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S02:E02- Naturally Noble
programme.desc: Zimbabwe was initially Southern Rhodesia and lies to the south of the Victoria Falls along the river Zambezi. Zambia was initially Northern Rhodesia and lies on the other bank of the river. Zimbabwe is a landlocked country in the south-east of Africa. It borders with South Africa to the south. According to archaeologists, the earliest records indicate that first human settlements in this area reach back to the 3rd century.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S02:E03 - Naturally Sustaining
programme.desc: We journey in search of incredible miracles of nature begins on the Canary Islands. Lanzarote is of a volcanic origin. Volcanic activity created a fantastical landscape, similar to that on Mars. On Gran Canarias we will witness a traditional harvest of a crop that has been brought to the rest of the world from here - sugarcane. We will wrap up this episode in the Moroccan province of Gulemin, a home to a nomadic tribe whose inseparable companions are camels.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S02:E04 - Naturally Colourful
programme.desc: Venture into the Mexican seaside state of Veracruz in the south-west of the country and admire the unbelievable colours of locally grown orchids. Find out how vanilla is grown and discover how brown sugar is made. To top things off, witness an extraordinary ritual. Later, we will visit the Cayman Islands in the Caribbean. The three islands are relatively small but are inhabited by some remarkable animals including sea turtles, friendly rays and other types of fish as well as fascinating blue iguanas.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S02:E05 - Naturally Enigmatic
programme.desc: Today we will visit three remarkable nooks of Europe in search of miracles of nature. To begin with, we will venture into Austria's Salzburg region. An area that is famous for its Alps and Tauern mountains but also because it is the birth place of Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart. After that, we will move over to the south western outpost of the old continent, to Portugal's Algarve region. To conclude, we will admire Corsica, the French island of beauty.

programme.title: 10 Inch Hero
programme.desc: An artist gets a job at a beachside sandwich shop, where she hangs out with a techie, a flirt, a rocker, a hippie, and a Wiccan.

programme.title: Alien Trespass
programme.desc: After crash landing on the outskirts of a desert town, an alien enlists the help of a local waitress to recapture a monster that has escaped the wreckage of his spaceship in this affectionate, knowing, hilarious send-up of a genreís sillier past.

programme.title: Eavesdrop
programme.desc: Ensemble drama about conversations overheard in a bistro: two chess players see unfolding dramas, a couple on an uncomfortable blind date, a crumbling marriage, and film-noir fans that think they're witnessing a real-life murder.

programme.title: Citizen Duane
programme.desc: CITIZEN DUANE is a comedy/drama about Duane Balfour a teen-aged Don Quixote born into a family of spectacular failure. What starts as a simple schoolyard rivalry snowballs out of control when Duane decides to run for mayor of the tiny town of Ridgeway. If Duane is to succeed, he must not only overcome the powerful incumbents, but also his own inadequacies, public perception, and history itself.

programme.title: Comedy Meets Classic
programme.desc: Created by British comedy duo Carrington-Brown, based in Berlin, and Irish conductor ClA�odhna NA� AodA�in, based in Switzerland. They join forces with "The Swonderful Orchestra" for this exciting, classy, and hilarious music & comedy show.

programme.title: Flirting With Flamenco
programme.desc: When Sylvia's well-meaning dad (Watt) surprises her with a devastating revelation, Sylvia's world is turned upside down. But will she crumble or prove herself at the local flamenco contest? An uplifting feel-good Brit comedy drama, Flirting with Flamenco will have you laughing, crying and feeling empowered to turn your life around.

programme.title: Citizen Duane
programme.desc: CITIZEN DUANE is a comedy/drama about Duane Balfour a teen-aged Don Quixote born into a family of spectacular failure. What starts as a simple schoolyard rivalry snowballs out of control when Duane decides to run for mayor of the tiny town of Ridgeway. If Duane is to succeed, he must not only overcome the powerful incumbents, but also his own inadequacies, public perception, and history itself.

programme.title: The Flying Deuces
programme.desc: When two bumbling friends join the French Foreign Legion on a whim, they find themselves in a whirlwind of misadventures, love, and laughter as they attempt to navigate the challenges of military life in a foreign land.

programme.title: Perfect Girl
programme.desc: A coming of age romance for anyone who's ever had a crush. Since high school, Stan and Jenny have had crushes on each other. They wrote letters to one another over school holidays but in person they barely spoke; sharing only the occasional lingering glance and smile. Over the years they fantasized about how perfect they would be as lovers. Ten years later they bump into each other and have the chance to make it a reality, but it's not that simple; self doubt, fear of rejection, of losing their fantasies will hold them back from what could be the perfect union.

programme.title: I Would Have Kissed You
programme.desc: Three months after college graduation, best friends Mattie and Olivia are struggling to write a feature and struggling even more with their love lives. programme.title: Whaddyado - Saving Pet
programme.desc: A 16-year-old teenager is struck by lightning and still survives. We’ll tell you what you should do if you find someone struck by lightning. *A dog trainer saves a dog’s life by giving it CPR. We’ll show you how to give CPR to help save your pet. * When a family’s car is stuck in the snow, they nearly die of carbon monoxide poisoning. We‘ll explain how carbon monoxide is the invisible killer and can be avoided. Our Moral Dilemma segment features the growing trend of sexual harassment at work.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Father Heart Attack
programme.desc: A three year old nearly drowns in his family’s swimming pool…he is rescued just in time by his five year old brother. *Father and son are walking home from a basketball game when the father suffers a heart attack…the son bravely gives him CPR and saves his life.*A critter has been disturbing a man’s bird feeder, so he sets up a motion detecting camera in his back yard…the very next night, he discovers it’s a huge black bear.* In our Moral Dilemma this week we take a hard look at teenage drivers and the dangerous distraction of their cell phones.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Kayaking
programme.desc: Camping…a group of teens that are a part of the “Venture Crew” with the boy scouts show us the right and wrong things to do when camping out. *A troublesome bear goes into a family’s home for their dinner leftovers. * Kayaking is a lot of fun but can turn dangerous when trying “White Water” paddling…what do you do if you find yourself in trouble. * A forest fire is approaching your home…have a plan here’s what to do.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Two Moms
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: You’ve made a new friend who’s trying to convince you to do some bad things. And instead of a mom and a dad this kid’s got two moms. Should it matter?

programme.title: ChatRoom - Peer Preasure
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: Peer pressure in the form of smoking. And spread the word, these words can hurt. Do you really need to say them?

programme.title: ChatRoom - Depression
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: Your friend seems depressed – how do you handle it? And he’s desperately trying to fit in, but does he have to lose himself in the process?

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - St. Kitts
programme.desc: Sunrise Yoga and a Golf lesson highlight Adventure Day One on the island of St. Kitts. We then paddled our way through the surf with sea kayaking and explored the “Valley of the Giants” as we hiked in St. Kitts’ rainforest. Day three began with learning the hot wax art form technique of Batik and concluded with a sunset catamaran cruise. Wrapping up our visit to “Sugar City” we checked out Brimstone Hill Fortress which sits atop one of the island’s highest peaks and then took in the stilt-dancing excitement of the Moko Jumbies.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Puerto Rico
programme.desc: We feel right at home in the United States Commonwealth of Puerto Rico this week. Day one takes us to El Yunque – the Caribbean National Rainforest – where we experience a natural water slide and swing around for even more fun. We then explore Old San Juan on day two before hopping on the jetskis for a high-speed water tour. On day three, we check out the dramatic Camuy Caves and drink in it’s natural beauty and atmosphere. We finish up on day four with an authentic Puerto Rican cooking lesson and a visit to the historic Arecibo Lighthouse.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Alaska
programme.desc: On toady’s show we’ll travel to the incredible state of Alaska. Watch as we climb the ice walls of the Mendenhall Glacier. We’ll also come face to face with a huge brown bear on Admiralty Island, and experience a fly-fishing adventure that we’ll never forget. Add in a little kayaking and some mountain biking and you have one Awesome Adventure!

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Suicide Race
programme.desc: If you think you love pets, then meet Jackie Jacobson, who’s got an awful lot of animals at her house! And visit an equestrian school in New Jersey to learn more about the beauty and excitement of this equine sport. It’s called “The Suicide Race” by its organizers: is it an innocent horse race steeped in tradition or is it outright abuse of these animals? Lastly, meet Ngoma and Tambo, one of the six sets of twin gorillas in captivity, at their home in the Bronx Zoo.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Belize Butterflies
programme.desc: This episode of “Wild About Animals” is devoted entirely to the beautiful country of Belize. You’ll learn all about the birds and the bees, along with some butterflies as we witness the magical birth of a magnificent creature. Next, we’ll visit a lodge in Belize where the guests can get up close and personal to an extremely mischievous monkey! And we’ll venture out into the Belizean jungle, a place where the evening entertainment is unconventional, to say the least.

programme.title: Ocean Animals
programme.desc: Join Emmy Award-winning Actress, Mariette Hartley, as she travels the globe to bring viewers fascinating stories!

programme.title: Whaddyado - Swine Flu
programme.desc: A 15-year-old teenager suffers from the Swine Flu and nearly dies. We’ll feature the symptoms in case you suffer from the Swine Flu. *A six-year-old boy is faced with a life threatening emergency and needs to call 9-1-1. *A man in Arizona is walking his dogs when a venomous rattlesnake bites him. We will tell you the steps to take in case a rattlesnake bites you. Our Moral Dilemma segment features the social problems caused by “mean girls.”

programme.title: Whaddyado - Shark Attack
programme.desc: A shark attacks and a surfer must ride the waves to escape to the safety of the beach. *A video surveillance system catches a near drowning on camera and the technology is the key to a young girl’s rescue. * A moral dilemma segment deals with peer pressure and the decision to get a tattoo.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Intruder
programme.desc: In this episode, a 12-year old is home alone, when an intruder breaks into his house. Two buddies are snowmobiling when an avalanche buries one of them. It will take a miracle to save him. A Florida family finds an unwelcome guest on their doorstep: A large alligator. And our Moral Dilemma looks at the growing problem of obesity.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Dropping Out of School
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: A friend is thinking about dropping out of school. What are his options? And she tries to laugh it off but mom has a serious drinking problem.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Bias
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: Mom’s prejudices are coming through loud and clear. And how high a price are you willing to pay to join the group?

programme.title: ChatRoom - Cheating
programme.desc: ChatRoom focuses on the ever-changing issues for today’s teens in a format that invites viewers to listen in on the conversation. This week’s topics include: She’s a little tipsy and he needs a ride, how do you handle it? And you forgot to study and there’s a pop quiz, what’s wrong with borrowing a few answers from a buddy?

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Minnesota
programme.desc: This week’s “Awesome Adventure” took us to the land of 10,000 lakes. We first learned how to hook up a team of dogs and let them take us for a ride on a dogsled. We then motored across frozen landscape in snowmobiles before traveling to Buck Hill for snowboarding, skiing and snow tubing. Next, we decided to spend some time indoors, so we headed to the Science Museum of Minnesota and slid over to the Grand Rios indoor water park. Since Minneapolis is home to the world famous Mall of America, we had to check out the mall that has it all. At the mall we visited the world’s largest underground aquarium, rode the Timberland Twister and made our own, Awesome Adventures-style fashion statement.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Canada
programme.desc: On this week’s episode of “Awesome Adventures,” we’ll travel to Canada to visit Vancouver Island, an adventure seekers paradise. We’ll work hand in hand to tackle a high ropes course, and climb the face of a 60 foot cliff. We’ll come face to face with black bears, and enormous whales. And we’ll experience the thrill of snorkeling down the Campbell River.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Curacao
programme.desc: This week it's off to the remote Caribbean island of Curacao.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Philadelphia Insectarium
programme.desc: Insects may seem creepy, but a lady at the Philadelphia Insectarium proves that bugs are fun. Next, you’ll meet Moose, one of the largest dogs in the world. Then we’ll travel out into the woods to learn more about bears. Finally, we’ll see a reptile show set in a school.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Best of 1995
programme.desc: This show features some of our favorite stories and moments from last season. We take you to incredible places like the Great Barrier Reef where you’ll learn and experience the underwater world of Australia. We also feature incredible animal rescue stories; the beautiful animals of Africa; as well as tips on learning how to care for our backyard creatures.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Vancouver Aquariam
programme.desc: This week on Wild About Animals we travel to Vancouver and visit the Marine Mammal Rescue Center. Researcher Bruce McCellan shows us how he uses hairs traps to research Grizzly bears. Then we meet up with Rob Hope of O.W.L. who introduces us to a rescued Great Horned Owl that is about to be released into the wild. And finally, we learn about 3 timber wolves, who were raised to be actors, but didn’t make it in the acting world and are now running free in Grouse Mountain.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Saving Pet
programme.desc: A 16-year-old teenager is struck by lightning and still survives. We’ll tell you what you should do if you find someone struck by lightning. *A dog trainer saves a dog’s life by giving it CPR. We’ll show you how to give CPR to help save your pet. * When a family’s car is stuck in the snow, they nearly die of carbon monoxide poisoning. We‘ll explain how carbon monoxide is the invisible killer and can be avoided. Our Moral Dilemma segment features the growing trend of sexual harassment at work.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Father Heart Attack
programme.desc: A three year old nearly drowns in his family’s swimming pool…he is rescued just in time by his five year old brother. *Father and son are walking home from a basketball game when the father suffers a heart attack…the son bravely gives him CPR and saves his life.*A critter has been disturbing a man’s bird feeder, so he sets up a motion detecting camera in his back yard…the very next night, he discovers it’s a huge black bear.* In our Moral Dilemma this week we take a hard look at teenage drivers and the dangerous distraction of their cell phones.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Kayaking
programme.desc: Camping…a group of teens that are a part of the “Venture Crew” with the boy scouts show us the right and wrong things to do when camping out. *A troublesome bear goes into a family’s home for their dinner leftovers. * Kayaking is a lot of fun but can turn dangerous when trying “White Water” paddling…what do you do if you find yourself in trouble. * A forest fire is approaching your home…have a plan here’s what to do.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Two Moms
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: You’ve made a new friend who’s trying to convince you to do some bad things. And instead of a mom and a dad this kid’s got two moms. Should it matter?

programme.title: ChatRoom - Peer Preasure
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: Peer pressure in the form of smoking. And spread the word, these words can hurt. Do you really need to say them?

programme.title: ChatRoom - Depression
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: Your friend seems depressed – how do you handle it? And he’s desperately trying to fit in, but does he have to lose himself in the process?

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - St. Kitts
programme.desc: Sunrise Yoga and a Golf lesson highlight Adventure Day One on the island of St. Kitts. We then paddled our way through the surf with sea kayaking and explored the “Valley of the Giants” as we hiked in St. Kitts’ rainforest. Day three began with learning the hot wax art form technique of Batik and concluded with a sunset catamaran cruise. Wrapping up our visit to “Sugar City” we checked out Brimstone Hill Fortress which sits atop one of the island’s highest peaks and then took in the stilt-dancing excitement of the Moko Jumbies.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Puerto Rico
programme.desc: We feel right at home in the United States Commonwealth of Puerto Rico this week. Day one takes us to El Yunque – the Caribbean National Rainforest – where we experience a natural water slide and swing around for even more fun. We then explore Old San Juan on day two before hopping on the jetskis for a high-speed water tour. On day three, we check out the dramatic Camuy Caves and drink in it’s natural beauty and atmosphere. We finish up on day four with an authentic Puerto Rican cooking lesson and a visit to the historic Arecibo Lighthouse.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Alaska
programme.desc: On toady’s show we’ll travel to the incredible state of Alaska. Watch as we climb the ice walls of the Mendenhall Glacier. We’ll also come face to face with a huge brown bear on Admiralty Island, and experience a fly-fishing adventure that we’ll never forget. Add in a little kayaking and some mountain biking and you have one Awesome Adventure!

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Suicide Race
programme.desc: If you think you love pets, then meet Jackie Jacobson, who’s got an awful lot of animals at her house! And visit an equestrian school in New Jersey to learn more about the beauty and excitement of this equine sport. It’s called “The Suicide Race” by its organizers: is it an innocent horse race steeped in tradition or is it outright abuse of these animals? Lastly, meet Ngoma and Tambo, one of the six sets of twin gorillas in captivity, at their home in the Bronx Zoo.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Belize Butterflies
programme.desc: This episode of “Wild About Animals” is devoted entirely to the beautiful country of Belize. You’ll learn all about the birds and the bees, along with some butterflies as we witness the magical birth of a magnificent creature. Next, we’ll visit a lodge in Belize where the guests can get up close and personal to an extremely mischievous monkey! And we’ll venture out into the Belizean jungle, a place where the evening entertainment is unconventional, to say the least.

programme.title: Ocean Animals
programme.desc: Join Emmy Award-winning Actress, Mariette Hartley, as she travels the globe to bring viewers fascinating stories!

programme.title: Whaddyado - Swine Flu
programme.desc: A 15-year-old teenager suffers from the Swine Flu and nearly dies. We’ll feature the symptoms in case you suffer from the Swine Flu. *A six-year-old boy is faced with a life threatening emergency and needs to call 9-1-1. *A man in Arizona is walking his dogs when a venomous rattlesnake bites him. We will tell you the steps to take in case a rattlesnake bites you. Our Moral Dilemma segment features the social problems caused by “mean girls.”

programme.title: Whaddyado - Shark Attack
programme.desc: A shark attacks and a surfer must ride the waves to escape to the safety of the beach. *A video surveillance system catches a near drowning on camera and the technology is the key to a young girl’s rescue. * A moral dilemma segment deals with peer pressure and the decision to get a tattoo.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Intruder

programme.title: Countdown To Apollo - The Mercury 7
programme.desc: Before Apollo, there was Gemini, and before Gemini, there was the Mercury program. This episode examines Mercury, the first U.S. program to put a man in space. It looks at the people, such as astronaut John Glenn, the events, such as Alan Shephard’s first flight to low earth orbit, and the triumphs of this precursor to Apollo.

programme.title: Countdown To Apollo - Firsts
programme.desc: This episode features the important “firsts” of the Apollo program. From the first satellite launched by the Soviets called Sputnick; to the first man who flew in space named Yuri Gagarin; the first spacewalk to the first live broadcast in space, many of the monumental achievements of the space race are documented.

programme.title: The Apollo Chronicles - Part 4 - Hailed As Heroes
programme.desc: Revel in the emotional achievement and lasting legacy of man’s first steps on the Moon.

programme.desc: The last man to walk on the moon was Gene Cernan on the Apollo 17 mission, in 1972. He said, “As we leave the moon, we leave as we came and God willing as we shall return. ”But with Nasa relying on government funding, the path back to the moon has been full of obstacles. This episode examines how each new President has their own vision of space exploration, and why this results in stops and starts in the space program.

The debate rages…on Xploration Outer Space.

programme.title: Stuart Cooper Films - The Craig Jones Story
programme.desc:
A short documentary telling the story of Craig Jones' sudden rise to success after his upset victory over Leandro Lo at ADCC 2017. After his breakout performance at ADCC, Craig went on to beat many more big names such as Jake Shields In Polaris, and made it to the finals of EBI, where he had a close finals match against Gordon Ryan. Since then Craig has competed in some of the biggest tournaments in the world and his life has changed dramatically. In this film we see that it wasn't always an easy road for him.
Director Stuart Cooper

programme.title: Tap Out Challenge - Oceanside
programme.desc: On October 15th at the picturesque Oceanside, CA, Charles Rials embarked on an incredible BJJ journey, challenging strangers from all walks of life to tap me out and claim $100. But there was a twist that none of them saw coming! Win or Lose, they got the MONEY!!! What they all shared was the courage to step up, the passion to engage, and the heart of a warrior. This video isn't just about BJJ or the challenge — it's a celebration of the human spirit, perseverance, and the unexpected twists that life (and jiu jitsu) can throw our way. Join Charles in this heartwarming, adrenaline-pumping journey where every challenge was met with respect, and every challenger was met with a surprise. Whether you're a BJJ enthusiast or someone who loves to witness genuine human moments, this video has something special for you.

programme.title: ADCC - Denver Opens
programme.desc: The Opens make their way to the mile high city where the best martial arts from the US look to stake their claim for supremacy as the circuit heats up. In this heart-pounding instalment, we bring you all the action from the epic showdown held in the magnificent city of Denver. Former UFC Strawweight Champion of the World Rose Namajunas known for her exceptional martial arts abilities, Rose is now ready to put her skills to the ultimate test in the realm of grappling. Witness her transition from the cage to the mats, as she grapples her way through some of the most intense matches of her career. ADCC Opens superstar and prodigy 16-year-old phenom, Helena Craver, steps onto the mats to showcase her unparalleled talent. With her sights set on glory, she aims to conquer the teenage, adults, and absolute divisions a feat that has never been done before. In a clash of titans, long time elite grappler Ryan Aitkens, a formidable competitor in his own right, is set to go head-to-head against the multiple-time world champion, Mateus Lutes. Brace yourself for an explosive battle between these two grappling juggernauts, as they leave everything on the mats in pursuit of victory.

programme.title: Just for Laughs Presents: Will Forte: The Time of Your Time
programme.desc: Saturday Night Live alumni and star of The Last Man on Earth, Will Forte, comes to Montreal to host one night of uproariously funny stand-up comedy in a special that can’t be missed. Featuring stand-out performances by Dylan Moran, Mario Joyner, Maria Bamford, Adam Christie, Cameron Esposito and Trent McClellan.

programme.title: Just for Laughs Presents: - Cheech & Chong : Puff Puff Laugh
programme.desc: The inventors of stoner comedy, legends Cheech & Chong are still jokin’ (and possibly smokin’). Catch them as they perform some of their funniest bits, recall some hilarious behind-the-scenes stories from their days of filming ‘Up In Smoke’ and host a full bag of the world’s funniest comedians. Included in the special are Last Comic Standing finalist Lavell Crawford, creator and star of the Brit cult comedy The Mighty Boosh Noel Fielding, the ever-opinionated Bill Burr, and Canada’s own rising star Jay Malone.

programme.title: Decline of the American Empire
programme.desc: Hosted by The Daily Show’s favourite Brit correspondent John Oliver, The Decline of the American Empire is the comedy dissection of our neighbours to the South… sort of a hilarious outsider’s State of the Union. It’s the smartest, most opinionated and politically-fuelled show in the lineup show, so get ready to piss your political trousers, speak your mind and have a look at the future, or lack thereof, of the USA.

Catch them as they perform some of their funniest bits, recall some hilarious behind-the-scenes stories from their days of filming ‘Up In Smoke’ and host a full bag of the world’s funniest comedians. Included in the special are Last Comic Standing finalist Lavell Crawford, creator and star of the Brit cult comedy The Mighty Boosh Noel Fielding, the ever-opinionated Bill Burr, and Canada’s own rising star Jay Malone.

programme.title: Decline of the American Empire
programme.desc: Hosted by The Daily Show’s favourite Brit correspondent John Oliver, The Decline of the American Empire is the comedy dissection of our neighbours to the South… sort of a hilarious outsider’s State of the Union. It’s the smartest, most opinionated and politically-fuelled show in the lineup show, so get ready to piss your political trousers, speak your mind and have a look at the future, or lack thereof, of the USA.

programme.desc: In "One Perfect Day in Kentucky," BFF’s Kimberly and Elsa bring their shared competitive streak to the Bluegrass State, facing off to find out who can plan the perfect Kentucky day. Each is determined to delight - and outdo - the other with unforgettable experiences that showcase the state's rich culture. Elsa kicks off the competition with a classic Kentucky breakfast, a recipe she learned from top Chef Ouita Michel at her Holly Hill Cooking Studio. Elsa wins the first point, but Kimberly’s ready to up the ante, whisking Elsa away for a thrilling cave kayaking adventure at the Gorge Underground. As they ride the chairlift to the top of the stunning Natural Bridge, the rivalry kicks into high gear and they go head-to-head in a trivia battle. The next surprise – a toast with Kentucky’s own Ale-8 soda , sourced by Kimberly straight from the factory only whets their whistles. At the Keeneland Racetrack they sip some spirit forward Keeneland Breezes while Elsa reveals all she has learned about racehorses from a visit to renowned trainer Mark Simms Jr. ‘s horse barn. A Betologist gives them a quick lesson on wagering and Kimberly’s horse wins the race. At Louisville’s Trouble Bar, Kimberly shares her newfound knowledge of Kentucky bourbon production from a tour and tasting at Castle + Key distillery and makes Elsa One Perfect Drink.

programme.desc: In "One Perfect Day in Kentucky," BFF’s Kimberly and Elsa bring their shared competitive streak to the Bluegrass State, facing off to find out who can plan the perfect Kentucky day. Each is determined to delight - and outdo - the other with unforgettable experiences that showcase the state's rich culture. Elsa kicks off the competition with a classic Kentucky breakfast, a recipe she learned from top Chef Ouita Michel at her Holly Hill Cooking Studio. Elsa wins the first point, but Kimberly’s ready to up the ante, whisking Elsa away for a thrilling cave kayaking adventure at the Gorge Underground. As they ride the chairlift to the top of the stunning Natural Bridge, the rivalry kicks into high gear and they go head-to-head in a trivia battle. The next surprise – a toast with Kentucky’s own Ale-8 soda , sourced by Kimberly straight from the factory only whets their whistles. At the Keeneland Racetrack they sip some spirit forward Keeneland Breezes while Elsa reveals all she has learned about racehorses from a visit to renowned trainer Mark Simms Jr. ‘s horse barn. A Betologist gives them a quick lesson on wagering and Kimberly’s horse wins the race. At Louisville’s Trouble Bar, Kimberly shares her newfound knowledge of Kentucky bourbon production from a tour and tasting at Castle + Key distillery and makes Elsa One Perfect Drink.

Each is determined to delight - and outdo - the other with unforgettable experiences that showcase the state's rich culture. Elsa kicks off the competition with a classic Kentucky breakfast, a recipe she learned from top Chef Ouita Michel at her Holly Hill Cooking Studio. Elsa wins the first point, but Kimberly’s ready to up the ante, whisking Elsa away for a thrilling cave kayaking adventure at the Gorge Underground. As they ride the chairlift to the top of the stunning Natural Bridge, the rivalry kicks into high gear and they go head-to-head in a trivia battle. The next surprise – a toast with Kentucky’s own Ale-8 soda , sourced by Kimberly straight from the factory only whets their whistles. At the Keeneland Racetrack they sip some spirit forward Keeneland Breezes while Elsa reveals all she has learned about racehorses from a visit to renowned trainer Mark Simms Jr. ‘s horse barn. A Betologist gives them a quick lesson on wagering and Kimberly’s horse wins the race. At Louisville’s Trouble Bar, Kimberly shares her newfound knowledge of Kentucky bourbon production from a tour and tasting at Castle + Key distillery and makes Elsa One Perfect Drink.

Joey struggles to keep himself together as the investigation leads him closer and closer to the deranged killer!

programme.title: The Faith Community
programme.desc: A group of religious students drive into the remote wilderness to spend time with a religious sect and strengthen their bond with God. The three unsuspecting students film everything to document their experience but soon find themselves in the dark.

programme.desc: A woman comes to New York City from Ohio to escape an abusive husband and gets entangled with murderous female vigilantes who prey on abusive men.

programme.title: Cut Her Out
programme.desc: Darcy can't purge her mind of the animalistic abuse she suffered as a child at the hands of her mother. Darcy's therapist Ryan discovers that her family homestead has been abandoned.

programme.title: Death Mask
programme.desc: Wilbur works in an old carnival and shows some gruesome things to the puplic. He covered his face because he had a sadistic father who burned his face. Everybody makes jokes about his scars and when the new boss fired him, he go to an old swamp-witch who gives him a peace of wood from a hanging tree and Wilbur makes a mask from this piece of wood and put all his anger in this mask. When he puts the mask on, everybody who looks on this mask commits suicide. He has created the Death-Mask.

programme.title: Hunting Season

programme.title: Temptation

programme.title: South Beach Classics
programme.desc: Need a classic car? If you're in Miami, where old-time autos fit in perfectly with the city's glitz and glamour, Ted Vernon is the man to see. The no-nonsense, gregarious Long Islander runs Florida's largest classic car dealership, where he buys, sells, trades and exchanges unique cars from a lot that houses more than 300 of them. His outgoing personality meshes seamlessly with the colourful collectibles he moves each day, helped by an eclectic shop crew affectionately dubbed `the gargoyles'.

programme.title: Titans of Business
programme.desc: There have been many stories and documentaries on the Bill Gates’, Steve Jobs’ and Henry Fords’ of the world. What about the thousands of other business people, that had a better idea or way to make life better, cheaper, and faster? People who started out from meager beginnings or limited education, to become very wealthy! Many of these people are among us and act no differently than we do, but they have a success story to tell and tricks of success to share. These are the people profiled in “Titans of Business”.

programme.title: Anchored in Paradise - Ep.7 - NOVALJA - RAB
Atlantic Cup - Episode 3
programme.desc: Welcome back to this edition of the Atlantic Cup. It is time for the third and final leg of the competition, the inshore series. Dragon and Gryphon Solo 2 are tied for, and teams have added 4 extra crew, allowing them to push their boats around the tight courses in Naragannset Bay. Any mistake could be the difference between first and last. Who will become the winner in this edition?

programme.title: International Canoe Federation World Cup - Sprint 3 World Championships Szeged
programme.desc: Welcome to the Canoe Sprint World Championships 2019 celebrated in Szeged, Hungary! Today there are about 1,200 athletes racing from approximately 98 nations, meaning this is the biggest World Championships canoe sprint racing has ever seen. We're about to witness the fastest paddlers on the planet battle it out for medals, for World Championship glory, and to qualify for their country at the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games. Enjoy the best moments at Szeged on the 2019 Sprint World Championships.

programme.title: International Canoe Federation World Cup - Slalom 1 World Cup Ljubljana
programme.desc: Ljubljana is the chosen scenery for the Slalom World Cup. The slovenian capital will bring the top kayakers who will navigate the whitewater course passing through a series of combination of upstream and downstream gates. The fastest to achieve this will become the champion of the World Cup. Find out now what will happen in Ljubljana in the exciting Slalom World Cup!

programme.title: Speed Catamarans GC32 - Episode 6
programme.desc: For its sixth season, the ultra-high performance one design catamarans, once again visited five top venues across the world. Each location selected particularly for its ideal weather conditions - stable winds and flat waters - perfect for the nimble GC32s to fly across the water at speeds of over 30 knots. Earlier in 2019, intensive discussions and decisions took place within the teams with many deciding to focus their efforts for the upcoming season, on the GC32 Racing Tour. This season the tour welcomed some new teams as well as many familiar regular GC32 crews. In total 12 teams from 9 different counties came together to take part in the 6th GC32 Racing Tour. Amongst them, some of the most well-known professional sailors in the world.

programme.title: H2O Racing: Aquabike World Championship - GP Spain - Ski
Sailing To Tokyo - Episode 3
programme.desc: Welcome to the third episode of Sailing to Tokyo! This time we move to Great Britain and the Weymouth and Portland National Sailing Academy to follow the Volvo 49er, 49erFX and Nacra 17 European Championship. This will be the first Olympic class racing event to take place in the UK since 2016! Are you coming with us?

programme.title: Reaching Reality - Episode 1 - Origin
programme.desc: From under the Golden Gate Bridge down to the Santa Cruz Islands the three friends and their little boat are now heading south. However bad weather is on the horizon and signs that the film and the filmmaker are already thinking about abandoning ship are starting to leak through. After a long night of sea sickness, it’s time to face reality and see who’s going to stick around and who’s going to go.

programme.title: Formula Wing European Championships - Ep.1 - URLA
New York - Vendée Transatlantic Race
programme.desc: This single-handed yacht race will cross the Northern Atlantic through two symbolic cities: New York and Sables d’Olonne. The departure from the Big Apple represents a cosmopolitan crossroad of influences, as well as the cradle of the IMOCA Class, while the arrival in the Sables d’Olonne means landing in the Old Continent after days or weeks of harsh conditions.After crossing a risky and challenging course straight through the middle of the “iceberg alley”, the skippers will arrive in the heart of the Vendée Globe considered as the “Everest of the Sea”. The Transatlantic race is the final event of the IMOCA Globe Series and it allows racers to build their hard racing miles. It represents a further opportunity to reinforce its image as a marine region, thus it is an awaited event for all those sailors thinking about embarking on the Vendée Globe.Follow their journey from New York to Sables d’Olonne in New York – Vendée Transatlantic Race. Available on Nautical Channel.

programme.title: Facing Waves - Ep5 - Kayaking Ireland\'s West Coast
programme.desc: Ken Whiting explores the Republic of Ireland\'s West Coast and the adventures by kayak and foot along the Wild Atlantic Way.

programme.title: Facing Waves - Ep6 - Great Family Adventure - Banff and Lake Louise, Canada
programme.desc: Pro kayakers Nick Troutman, Emily Jackson and family try some winter activities on for size in beautiful Banff and Lake Louise, Canada.

programme.title: Durban Extravaganza
programme.desc: Durban: a coastal city in eastern South Africa’s KwaZulu-Natal province known for its diverse influences and for hosting the Durban Extravaganza. The City of Durban and Durban Stars have brought the heat to the beautiful beachfront with the Surfing South Africa sanctioned Pro Surf Tour competition. Over 3 three days, the top 100 surfers gather in the South African city to participate in the hottest surfing competition of the African country.You can expect high-level competition with waves that are over 2-3 foot in Durban Extravaganza. Competing at the Bay of Plenty, surfers will surely dive in for plenty of action. A fanta-SEA for surf lovers!

programme.title: Nautical Adventure In A Landlocked Country
programme.desc: Switzerland: home to the Alps and important water competitions like the Bol d’Or Mirabaud, the most important inland lake regatta in the world. Today it becomes the chosen scenario for this Nautical Adventure in a Landlocked Country. From extreme wakeboarding to canoe polo, we will discover that, despite being located far from the sea, Switzerland has a vibrant nautical scene.Get ready to accompany Nautical Channel’s host, Lucia Metzbauer, as she goes wakeboarding with local Swiss pros, learns about the annual Match Race regatta, tries her hand at Stand-Up-Paddle, and discovers the little known sport of Canoe Polo! This country has much to offer, so don’t miss out on its beautiful scenery that will have you pack your bags to come visit on the first occasion.Nautical Adventure in a Landlocked Country reminds us that water sports can be practiced even in countries that do not border the ocean. An inland fanta-sea for those nautical intrepids that are looking for ways of widening their horizons. Welcome to the Alps.

programme.title: Anchored in Paradise - Ep.7 - NOVALJA - RAB
Atlantic Cup - Episode 3
programme.desc: Welcome back to this edition of the Atlantic Cup. It is time for the third and final leg of the competition, the inshore series. Dragon and Gryphon Solo 2 are tied for, and teams have added 4 extra crew, allowing them to push their boats around the tight courses in Naragannset Bay. Any mistake could be the difference between first and last. Who will become the winner in this edition?

programme.title: Kite Masters - Episode 5
programme.desc: There are two elements that grabbed our attention during the 2020 Formula Kite Mixed Relay European Championships: the UK’s Connor Bainbridge and the Polish team.Along with his teammate Elli Aldridge, Connor managed to defend his European title. Meanwhile, the Polish team was the great surprise of the championship, having two out of their six teams qualifying to the gold fleet. After that, we will focus on the Kite venues hosting the hottest action from the kite events.We will discover why riders love these locations and what makes the International Kiteboarding Association so confident in the venues. Finally, we reencounter four-time world champion, Daniela Moroz, who shared some more golden Kiteboarding tips.

programme.title: Kite Masters - Episode 6
programme.desc: As we come to the end of the 2020 series, we'll take a look back over all the happenings earlier this season in the extreme world of kiteboarding as well as the transformation of the sport on the road to Paris 2024.Later on, we are set to find out what happened during the last event of the season, the 2020 KiteFoil European Championships taking place in Playa de las Burras, Gran Canaria, Spain. We end our journey travelling to the USA to meet one of the most popular riders in the world: Daniela Moroz.

Over 3 three days, the top 100 surfers gather in the South African city to participate in the hottest surfing competition of the African country.You can expect high-level competition with waves that are over 2-3 foot in Durban Extravaganza. Competing at the Bay of Plenty, surfers will surely dive in for plenty of action. A fanta-SEA for surf lovers!

programme.title: Nautical Adventure In A Landlocked Country
programme.desc: Switzerland: home to the Alps and important water competitions like the Bol d’Or Mirabaud, the most important inland lake regatta in the world. Today it becomes the chosen scenario for this Nautical Adventure in a Landlocked Country. From extreme wakeboarding to canoe polo, we will discover that, despite being located far from the sea, Switzerland has a vibrant nautical scene.Get ready to accompany Nautical Channel’s host, Lucia Metzbauer, as she goes wakeboarding with local Swiss pros, learns about the annual Match Race regatta, tries her hand at Stand-Up-Paddle, and discovers the little known sport of Canoe Polo! This country has much to offer, so don’t miss out on its beautiful scenery that will have you pack your bags to come visit on the first occasion.Nautical Adventure in a Landlocked Country reminds us that water sports can be practiced even in countries that do not border the ocean. An inland fanta-sea for those nautical intrepids that are looking for ways of widening their horizons. Welcome to the Alps.

programme.title: Speed Catamarans GC32 - Episode 6
programme.desc: For its sixth season, the ultra-high performance one design catamarans, once again visited five top venues across the world. Each location selected particularly for its ideal weather conditions - stable winds and flat waters - perfect for the nimble GC32s to fly across the water at speeds of over 30 knots. Earlier in 2019, intensive discussions and decisions took place within the teams with many deciding to focus their efforts for the upcoming season, on the GC32 Racing Tour. This season the tour welcomed some new teams as well as many familiar regular GC32 crews. In total 12 teams from 9 different counties came together to take part in the 6th GC32 Racing Tour. Amongst them, some of the most well-known professional sailors in the world.

programme.title: H2O Racing: Aquabike World Championship - GP Spain - Ski
Sailing To Tokyo - Episode 3
programme.desc: Welcome to the third episode of Sailing to Tokyo! This time we move to Great Britain and the Weymouth and Portland National Sailing Academy to follow the Volvo 49er, 49erFX and Nacra 17 European Championship. This will be the first Olympic class racing event to take place in the UK since 2016! Are you coming with us?

programme.title: Reaching Reality - Episode 1 - Origin
programme.desc: From under the Golden Gate Bridge down to the Santa Cruz Islands the three friends and their little boat are now heading south. However bad weather is on the horizon and signs that the film and the filmmaker are already thinking about abandoning ship are starting to leak through. After a long night of sea sickness, it’s time to face reality and see who’s going to stick around and who’s going to go.

programme.title: Formula Wing European Championships - Ep.1 - URLA
New York - Vendée Transatlantic Race
programme.desc: This single-handed yacht race will cross the Northern Atlantic through two symbolic cities: New York and Sables d’Olonne. The departure from the Big Apple represents a cosmopolitan crossroad of influences, as well as the cradle of the IMOCA Class, while the arrival in the Sables d’Olonne means landing in the Old Continent after days or weeks of harsh conditions.After crossing a risky and challenging course straight through the middle of the “iceberg alley”, the skippers will arrive in the heart of the Vendée Globe considered as the “Everest of the Sea”. The Transatlantic race is the final event of the IMOCA Globe Series and it allows racers to build their hard racing miles. It represents a further opportunity to reinforce its image as a marine region, thus it is an awaited event for all those sailors thinking about embarking on the Vendée Globe.Follow their journey from New York to Sables d’Olonne in New York – Vendée Transatlantic Race. Available on Nautical Channel.

programme.title: International Canoe Federation World Cup - Sprint 1 World Cup Szeged
programme.desc: Szeged in Hungary is the third biggest city in the country and the chosen scenery for the Sprints World Cup. Organisers of the ICF canoe sprint moved heaven and earth to prove an international event in the middle of a global pandemic was possible and safe for all participants. As a result, athletes took part in a splendid competition.

programme.title: International Canoe Federation World Cup - Slalom 2 World Cup Pau
programme.desc: The Slalom World Cup series of 2020 continue in Pau. In the south of France, just 85km from the Spanish border, the kayakers will challenge themselves to this slalom competition. They want to become the best of the world in this Olympic discipline. Find out now who will be at the podium of the Slalom World Cup in Pau.

programme.title: Anchored in Paradise - Ep.7 - NOVALJA - RAB
Atlantic Cup - Episode 3
programme.desc: Welcome back to this edition of the Atlantic Cup. It is time for the third and final leg of the competition, the inshore series. Dragon and Gryphon Solo 2 are tied for, and teams have added 4 extra crew, allowing them to push their boats around the tight courses in Naragannset Bay. Any mistake could be the difference between first and last. Who will become the winner in this edition?

programme.desc: Welcome to Salzburg for the second leg of the FEI Dressage World Cup. We are in Austria to see some of the very best horse and rider combinations in the sport. programme.desc: The mythical Tropicana Derby is one of the categories inside the Jumping International de Dinard, and it offers a combination of traditional and natural fences over a particularly long distance of 1100m that will bring both horse and rider to their limit. Relive the best moments of Dinards Tropicana Derby with a jumping height over 1.45m.

programme.title: Dressage Season Review - Episode 1
programme.desc: The best action in the dressage world is ready for the 2016/2017 edition. Riders prepare themselves for this arduous challenge that give us some of the most magical moments in equestrian sports. Be part of the excitement that moves across Europe, the Americas and the Pacific in the 2016/2017 Dressage World Cup Season.

programme.title: Longines FEI Jumping Nations Cup - Abu Dhabi
FEI Rides Magazine - Episode 4: Horsewomen
programme.desc: This week Ride celebrates three extraordinary horsewomen and the captivating connection they have with their equine friends. We showcase exhebition work from American dressage star Sabine Schut-Kery, experience life through a lens with Poland’s fine art horse photographer Katarzyna Okrzesik-Mikolajek, and witness the holistic approach to healing in South West England with renowned trainer Connie Cox.

programme.title: FEI Rides Magazine - Episode 5: Heroes & Healers
programme.desc: This week Ride exercises military precision with the mounts of the Household Cavalry at the British Army’s London Barracks, and sees second chances given to troubled residents at Achterhoek horse shelter in the Netherlands. We’re in the back seat with Polish driving expert Piotr Mazurek and catch up with this year’s Longines FEI Rising Star Award winner, Germany’s Greta Busacker.

programme.title: Longines Global Champions Tour - Episode 8 - Stockholm
programme.desc: The Swedish capital of Stockholm is the host of the eighth leg of the Longines Global Champions Tour 2022: the international circuit that challenges top-riders from around the world in individual show jumping. programme.title: Longines Global Champions Tour - Episode 17 - Prague
Dressage Season Review - Review
programme.desc: The Grand Prix at the final in Gothenburg will be disputed with Freestyle with music, and it will be extremely difficult. programme.title: Longines FEI Jumping Nations Cup - Barcelona
Campus Life Experience - Episode 6
programme.desc: In this new episode, we first realize the vet check to determine whether the horse is in good physical condition to take part in the competition. Once everything is fine with our horses, we check our rider's boots and then get a good night sleep as we will have to wake up at 6 for Manuel's class.

programme.title: Campus Life Experience - Episode 7
programme.desc: The educational program that lasted a week is finally reaching its end.
